IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF THE KENTUCKY CATTLEMEN'S ASSOCIATION IS THE PROMOTION OF THE BEEF INDUSTRY.
IRS990.Desc: CHECKOFF PROGRAM - PROMOTION OF THE BEEF INDUSTRY IN KENTUCKY THROUGH RESEARCH, EDUCATION, ADVERTISING, AND INDUSTRY INFORMATION SERVICES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: KENTUCKY BEEF NETWORK COORDINATES EFFORTS OF THE STATE'S BEEF PRODUCERS THROUGH EDUCATION, MARKETING, AND DEVELOPMENT OF VALUE-ADDED INITIATIVES THAT HAVE INCREASED THE NET INCOME OF THE BEEF PRODUCERS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: INFORMATION SERVICES - KEEP THE PUBLIC AND BEEF PRODUCERS INFORMED ABOUT MATTERS RELATED TO THE BEEF INDUSTRY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ASSOCIATION IS EXEMPT FROM TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(A) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. HOWEVER, THE ASSOCIATION IS SUBJECT TO FEDERAL INCOME TAX ON ANY UNRELATED BUSINESS TAXABLE INCOME. THE ASSOCIATION RECORDED AN ACCRUAL FOR TAXES RELATING TO ADVERTISING INCOME FROM ITS MONTHLY PUBLICATION, COW COUNTRY NEWS, MANAGEMENT FEES FROM THE LIVESTOCK ADVERTISING NETWORK, AND PROFIT ON BEEF SALES FROM BEEF SOLUTIONS, LLC OF $34,922 AND $6,240 IN 2018 AND 2017, RESPECTIVELY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DUE TO THE NATURE OF THE INDUSTRY, IT IS POSSIBLE THAT CERTAIN DIRECTORS COULD HAVE BUSINESS RELATIONSHIPS WITH ONE ANOTHER. THE ORGANIZATION IS NOT AWARE OF ANY RELATIONSHIPS AT THIS TIME.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR WILL REVIEW FORM 990 PRIOR TO FILING. A COPY OF FORM 990 IS HELD AT THE OFFICE FOR BOARD MEMBERS' REVIEW UPON REQUEST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AN ANNUAL ORIENTATION AT THE FEBRUARY BOARD MEETING PRESENTS THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND BOARD MEMBERS WILL BE ASKED TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AN EVALUATION COMMITTEE, MADE UP OF BOARD MEMBERS, MAKES COMPENSATION DECISIONS BASED UPON REVIEW OF PRIOR YEAR FINANCIALS AND COMPARABLE MARKET DATA.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
